@swissjoe . . . You need to shut up because what you are saying isn't true. Telesync has NOTHING to do with the quality of video. Telesync means that the audio was recorded using an external audio source. IE, plugging sound directly into recorder before going to speakers. R5 is DVD quality. Cam and TS are recorded visually the same way. Yeah, one may be in the booth, another in the seats. But that doesn't have anything to do with those little letters people put next to their posts.
